The paper focuses on recent advances in learning-based approaches for biomedical information extraction, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases).
